Spells:
  Hellish Rebuke:
    Casting Time: reaction:1
    Range: 60
    Components: Vocal,Symatic
    Duration: Instataneous
    Description: [[
You point your finger, and the creature that damaged you is momintarily
surrounded by flames. The creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. It takes
2d10 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.

Reaction in response to taking damage.
]]
  Hex:
    Casting Time: bonus action
    Range: 90
    Components: Vocal, Symatic
    Duration: concentration, max:1:hr
    Description: [[
You place a curse on a creature that you can see within range. Until the
spell ends, you deal an extra 1d6 necrotic damage to the target whenever you
hit it with an attack. Also, choose one ability when you cast the spell. The
target has disadvantage on ability checks made with the chosen ability.

If the target drops to 0 hit points before this spell ends, you can use a
bonus action on a subsequent turn of yours to curse a new creature.]]
